where formula_249 is the Lie bracket.

A &quot;Levi-Civita connection&quot; is a torsion-free connection that preserves the metric. Once a Riemannian metric is fixed, there exists a unique Levi-Civita connection. Note that the definition of preserving the metric uses the regularity of formula_11.

